<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 1116/81 of 28 April 1981 amending Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 in respect of lemons and Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 in respect of lemons and preventive withdrawals of apples and pears </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1116/81, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 sidrunite puhul ja m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 sidrunite puhul ning ennetava &otilde;unade ja pirnide turult k&otilde;rvaldamise puhul 28. aprill 1981 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 6 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 of 9 December 1969 laying down special measures for improving the production and marketing of Community citrus fruit (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1367/80 (5) extended the granting of financial compensation for the marketing of lemons until the end of the 1980/81 marketing year; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 9. detsembri 1969. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 (millega s&auml;testatakse erimeetmed &uuml;henduse tsitrusviljade tootmise ja turustamise parandamiseks, (4) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1367/80 (5)) artikliga 6 pikendatakse rahalise h&uuml;vitise maksmist sidrunite turustamiseks kuni 1980/81. turustusaasta l&otilde;puni; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these measures have encouraged the marketing of better quality products; whereas such a trend should be furthered by retaining these measures in the coming marketing year; whereas, therefore, when the reference price for lemons is calculated, account should not be taken of the transport costs as defined in Article 23 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 of 18 May 1972 on the common organization of the market in fruit and vegetables (6), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1367/80; </inglise>
<eesti> need meetmed on aidanud kaasa parema kvaliteediga toodete turustamisele; seda arengutendentsi tuleks soodustada nende meetmete s&auml;ilitamisega j&auml;rgnevaks turustusaastaks; seet&otilde;ttu ei tule sidrunite v&otilde;rdlushinna arvutamisel arvesse v&otilde;tta n&otilde;ukogu 18. mai 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (6) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1367/80, m&auml;&auml;ratletud veokulusid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 15a of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 provides that preventive withdrawals may be authorized for apples and pears where the market situation gives reason to fear a collapse of the market and heavy withdrawals and where producer prices fall below certain levels; whereas experience in the last two marketing years shows that the effectiveness of these preventive withdrawals would be improved if the decision authorizing them could be taken solely on the basis of an examination of the market situation, </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artiklis 15a on s&auml;testatud ennetava turult k&otilde;rvaldamise lubamine &otilde;unte ja pirnide puhul, juhul kui turuolukorrast tulenevalt on karta turukrahhi ja laialdast turult k&otilde;rvaldamist ning kui tootjahinnad on teatavast tasemest madalamad; kahe eelmise turustusaasta kogemused on n&auml;idanud, et ennetava turult k&otilde;rvaldamise t&otilde;husust on v&otilde;imalik t&otilde;sta, kui selle lubamise v&otilde;ib otsustada ainult turuolukorra anal&uuml;&uuml;si p&otilde;hjal, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In the second paragraph of Article 6 of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69, "1 June 1981" shall be replaced by "1 June 1982". </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 artikli 6 teises l&otilde;igus asendatakse kuup&auml;ev "1. juuni 1981" kuup&auml;evaga "1. juuni 1982". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 15a of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72, paragraph I shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artikli 15a l&otilde;ige 1 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "1. </inglise>
<eesti> "1. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards apples and pears, if examination of the market situation and particularly of the volume of production and the price levels shows the risk of a collapse of the market and of heavy withdrawals of one or both of the products concerned, it may be decided, in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 33, that the Member States may authorize producers' organizations to withdraw, during the first months of the marketing year, a proportion of the products which comply with the minimum specifications of the quality standards in force. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &otilde;unade ja pirnide puhul ilmneb turuolukorra ja eelk&otilde;ige tootmismahu ja hinnataseme uurimisel turukrahhi ja &uuml;he v&otilde;i m&otilde;lema nimetatud toote turult k&otilde;rvaldamise oht, v&otilde;ib artiklis 33 s&auml;testatud korras v&otilde;tta vastu otsuse, et liikmesriik v&otilde;ib lubada tootjaorganisatsioonidel turustusaasta esimeste kuude jooksul k&otilde;rvaldada osa selliseid tooteid, mis vastavad kehtivate kvaliteedistandardite miinimumn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> When a producers' organization makes use of this authorization, it shall grant to member producers an indemnity, calculated on the basis of the withdrawal price referred to in Article 15, in respect of the quantities of products withdrawn. " </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tootjaorganisatsioon kasutab seda luba, annab ta liikmetest tootjatele k&otilde;rvaldatud toote koguste osas artiklis 15 s&auml;testatud k&otilde;rvaldamishinna alusel arvutatud h&uuml;vitist. " </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> In the first indent of the first subparagraph of Article 23 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72, "31 May 1981" shall be replaced by "31 May 1982". </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artikli 23 l&otilde;ike 2 esimese l&otilde;igu esimeses taandes asendatakse kuup&auml;ev "31. mai 1981" kuup&auml;evaga "31. mai 1982". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply with effect from 1 June 1981. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. juulist 1980. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
